1
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:05,300
<i>ALLISON:
Dread becomes unannounced and then consumes our feelings</i>

2
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:08,000
<i>with its irrational
sense of doom.</i>

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,300
<i>Have you ever had
the feeling of dread?</i>

4
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:19,100
<i>I'm not talking about fear.</i>

5
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:20,200
<i>Fear is immediate.</i>

6
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,100
<i>Fear is what kicks in when you're
confronted with danger</i>

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,200
<i>A mugger with a gun.</i>

8
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,400
<i>A stranger in your house.</i>

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,800
<i>I'm talking about dread.</i>

10
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>Dread is persistent.</i>

11
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,200
<i>It gnaws at you.</i>

12
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,900
<i>You can't ignore it.</i>

13
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:39,400
<i>It just won't go away.</i>

14
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>Because that's what dread is.</i>

15
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:46,900
<i>It's worrying about something
you can't do anything about.</i>

16
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:48,800
<i>Dread can affect your job,</i>

17
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>your home, alter your entire
personality.</i>

18
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,300
Hey, sorry to wake you.

19
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:01,000
I felt funny leaving
without saying good-bye.

20
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,800
It's so early.
I know.

21
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:06,900
My ride said he needed
to get in before everybody else.

22
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,300
Your ride?
Yeah.
Remember?

23
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,300
I dropped my car off at the shop
on the way home last night.

24
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:13,700
Oh, right.

25
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,400
I thought I was driving you.

26
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,100
No, I told you.

27
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,400
I looked through
the company directory and I made

28
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:22,100
some phone calls-- I got a guy
from work to take me.

29
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,500
What's with the long face?

30
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:28,600
I don't know.
Funny feeling, like...

31
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:32,700
Like you're...
I'm supposed to drive you or...

32
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,100
Maybe you're not
supposed to go at all.

33
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,500
You hear that?

34
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,700
Maybe it's the world's
way of telling us

35
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,800
to stay in bed, just...

36
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,500
let a day go by without us.

37
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:46,900
I'll let you explain
that to my bosses.

38
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,600
Today's the monthly project
management meeting.

39
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,700
But I'm sure they'd be happy
to call it on account of rain.

40
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,000
That's my ride.
Are you sure

41
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:57,500
you don't want
me to drive you?

42
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,500
I have a funny feeling.
No, it's fine. Really.

43
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,300
If you want to do
something for me,

44
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:06,400
if it clears, maybe you can
swing by the dry cleaners

45
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,100
and pick up my shirts.

46
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,600
That would be...
(doorbell rings)

47
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,000
Can you grab that?
I'm just going to get my bag.

48
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,900
Hi, uh, I'm Bruce.
I'm here for Joe.

49
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:17,800
Oh, yeah. Come in, come in.

50
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:19,900
I'm Allison, I'm Joe's wife.

51
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,100
Hope you brought your ark.

52
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,300
Um, well, let me just...

53
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:32,100
Uh, check on Joe,
see what he's up to.

54
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,000
Hey, sorry to wake you, but...

55
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,900
You felt funny leaving
without saying good-bye.

56
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:44,600
Yeah.

57
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:47,000
I need you to say home.

58
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:49,000
Honey, that's my ride.

59
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,700
No, I mean it.
I really need you to stay home.

60
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:53,600
Okay. Can you tell me why?

61
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,400
No. A feeling.

62
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,100
Maybe it's the rain.

63
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:00,100
Maybe it's the thunder.

64
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:02,800
Okay, well, the rain
is going to stop,

65
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,300
and the thunder will pass.

66
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:05,600
I really need to go to work.

67
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:08,400
The kids really need to go
to school, not to mention...

68
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,900
I know. Your shirts,
the cleaners...

69
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,800
Big meeting. Wish me luck.

70
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,200
Luck...

71
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:19,500
